<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 761.91/55</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-13T18:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>75. Your 10 a.m., August 1, and 11 a.m., August 4, and Department’s 6
                            p.m., August 7. Ascertain discreetly and report fully and promptly
                            attitude all foreign legations, particularly German, Austrian and
                            Turkish, relative to decree of Persian Cabinet. Department desires to
                            receive all possible facts and suggestions relative to this matter.
                            Instruct <persName corresp="#p_SAE1">Southard</persName> also to
                            investigate and report his views.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>